Author-Name: JIANG WANG 
Title: Trading Volume: Implications of an Intertemporal Capital Asset Pricing Model 
Abstract:
 We derive an intertemporal asset pricing model and explore its
 implications for trading volume and asset returns. We show that investors
 trade in only two portfolios: the market portfolio, and a hedging
 portfolio that is used to hedge the risk of changing market conditions. We
 empirically identify the hedging portfolio using weekly volume and returns
 data for U.S. stocks, and then test two of its properties implied by the
 theory: Its return should be an additional risk factor in explaining the
 cross section of asset returns, and should also be the best predictor of
 future market returns. Copyright 2006 by The American Finance Association. 
