Author-Name: ALEXEI JILTSOV 
Title: Model Uncertainty and Option Markets with Heterogeneous Beliefs 
Abstract:
 This paper provides option pricing and volume implications for an economy
 with heterogeneous agents who face model uncertainty and have different
 beliefs on expected returns. Market incompleteness makes options
 nonredundant, while heterogeneity creates a link between differences in
 beliefs and option volumes. We solve for both option prices and volumes
 and test the joint empirical implications using S&P500 index option data.
 Specifically, we use survey data to build an Index of Dispersion in
 Beliefs and find that a model that takes information heterogeneity into
 account can explain the dynamics of option volume and the smile better
 than can reduced-form models with stochastic volatility. Copyright 2006 by The American Finance Association. 
