Author-Name: LI YONG 
Author-Name: LU ZHENG 
Title: Tax-Loss Selling and the January Effect: Evidence from Municipal Bond Closed-End Funds 
Abstract:
 This paper provides direct evidence supporting the tax-loss selling
 hypothesis as an explanation of the January effect. Examining
 turn-of-the-year return and volume patterns for municipal bond closed-end
 funds, which are held mostly by tax-sensitive individual investors, we
 document a January effect for these funds, but not for their underlying
 assets. We provide evidence that this effect can be largely explained by
 tax-loss selling activities at the previous year-end. Moreover, we find
 that funds associated with brokerage firms display more tax-loss selling
 behavior, suggesting that tax counseling plays a role. Copyright 2006 by The American Finance Association. 
